article.description: Bonnie Samuelson leads No. 13 Stanford past Arizona 77-47
article.headline: Bonnie Samuelson leads No. 13 Stanford past Arizona 77-47
article.linkText: Bonnie Samuelson leads No. 13 Stanford past Arizona 77-47
article.story:
STANFORD, Calif. -- Bonnie Samuelson had 14 points, and Erica McCall had 13 and a career-high 16 rebounds to lead No. 13 Stanford to a 77-47 win over Arizona on Friday.

Karlie Samuelson, Lili Thompson and Brianna Roberson had 12 points apiece for the Cardinal (13-4, 5-0 Pac-12), who have won six straight.

Breanna Workman made 6 of 8 shots with 12 points to lead the Wildcats (7-9, 0-5), who shot 36 percent.

Stanford rolled to a 41-24 lead at the half, making 4 of 8 3-pointers and shooting 53.3 percent. Roberson had 10 points.

The Cardinal took control early with a 13-0 run highlighted by Bonnie Samuelson sandwiching 3-pointers around her sister's 3 on consecutive possessions, to lead 17-4.

In one later 18-second stretch McCall had a block and rebound before grabbing two of her own misses and converting the putback.
